    <title>DevOps Showdown: The Technologist vs. The Sales Guy</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/devops-showdown-technologist-vs-sales-guy</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Embracing new technologies is difficult, especially for seasoned I.T. veterans with established workflows. In this session we will demonstrate the most productive path from idea to implementation and the difference that DevOps and workflow automation can make for Information Technology providers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In order to drive our point we are going to take a shot at the old fashioned “do everything manually” workflow cycle, by pitting Dan Reif, Director of Engineering at BlackMesh, against Aaron Porter, Partnership Sales Lead at BlackMesh, in a head to head competition. We will be focusing on the speed at which code changes can be committed across different environments and aim to unequivocally demonstrate that without DevOps you’re working in the past, and your standard workflow is about to become extinct.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Come and watch the fun as two people working at opposite ends of an organization square off to demonstrate the DevOps difference…&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;***This session will be just as much Business Strategy as DevOps/Coding &amp;amp; although it is being listed as intermediate, it will not be too technical for beginners and it will not be too basic for advanced.***&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Porter.Aaron1&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/code-and-devops&quot;&gt;Code and DevOps&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
