  <item>
    <title>You&#039;ve won a contract to do Drupal development using Agile. So what&#039;s next?</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/youve-won-contract-do-drupal-development-using-agile-so-whats-next</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Your company is so lucky and just won a Drupal project. After the celebration, what is the next thing you have to do? You are going to build a brand new Drupal site. Where should you start?&amp;nbsp; We all want to do it right at first time to avoid rework. We want to use Agile timeboxed development to have early and frequent delivery to get customer feedback. But, Drupal has so many modules, which one should be build first? How could we build it right with Agile development cycles? This workshop is to demonstrate and practice a success model you could adopt to build your new Drupal site and to meet customer’s expectations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Featured Participants: This workshop is targeting both federal agency who issuing a Drupal contract and vendors who won a new Drupal site and may win the contract in the future.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Keywords: Drupal Site Agile Development Learning Outcome: Learn how to build a new Drupal with Agile development cycles&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agenda:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1-1:15 PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Introduction&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Why Apply Agile to Drupal Development&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sprint 0 Model&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Sprint Cadence&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Definition of Done&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Drupal Product Roadmap&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1:15-1:40 PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Simulation to Produce A Drupal Prototype Site&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Selected Team Presentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1:40-1:45 PM&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Concludes and Summarizes the session&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-slides field--type-file field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Slides:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;file&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;file-icon&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;application/pdf&quot; src=&quot;/modules/file/icons/application-pdf.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/sites/2015.drupalgovcon.org/files/slides/Drupal%20Agile%20v.10.pdf&quot; type=&quot;application/pdf; length=1650729&quot;&gt;Drupal Agile v.10.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;ssone@bstonetech.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;mspyker@bstonetech.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;winternett@hotmail.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;dhouse@bstonetech.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;heatherchoi@hotmail.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;jrobertson@bstonetech.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;quentin.carissimo@gmail.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;hdbaines@gmail.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-timeslot field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Time Slot(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots clearfix&quot; class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots&quot;&gt;
