  <item>
    <title>Building Realtime Applications with Drupal and Node.js</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/building-realtime-applications-drupal-and-nodejs</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Call it the &quot;appification&quot; of the web. Users&#039; expectations are being pushed in the direction of being able to interact with sites and content not by clicking a link or refreshing the page but by having those changes come directly to them. Think Google Mail or Facebook or Twitter, updates that engage the user when they happen rather than waiting for them to have to keep checking back. With Drupal 8 having a first class REST interface a world of opportunities open up. Unfortunately PHP isn&#039;t always the best language for this sort of behavior. But we live in a polyglot world, and Node.js is perfect for this sort of work. In this session you&#039;ll learn how to connect a Node application to Drupal to allow updates to be seen when they happen. We&#039;ll be using Drupal, AngularJS and Sails.js to demonstrate the capabilities of both Javascript and Node to build interactive applications and synchronize with Drupal through the REST interface to serve as the data repository.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other references:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1ljw3VykvZGDjpqI6_BbRoSq0CrK7AJkhIe5O3uMb9bA/pub?start=false&amp;amp;loop=false&amp;amp;delayms=3000&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Slides&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/forumone/realtime-apps-drupal-sails&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;whurley@forumone.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-timeslot field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Time Slot(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots clearfix&quot; class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-timeslot-time field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Time:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;07/23/2015 - 15:00-07/23/2015 - 15:45&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-timeslot-room field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Room:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Auditorium&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;
