  <item>
    <title>Integrating Your Technical and Communications Teams</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/integrating-your-technical-and-communications-teams</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Very often, digital teams work in two or three strongly-defined silos. There is a content team and a&amp;nbsp;development team, and sometimes there is a design team that works between those two groups. Little&amp;nbsp;conversation happens between those groups, and they often work towards the finish line of a project with&amp;nbsp;an unproductive and unhealthy animosity towards each other, all while playing tug-of-war with the&amp;nbsp;designers that must support both teams. The finished product produced by these groups never reaches its&amp;nbsp;potential because the teams that produce don’t know how to ideate, plan and execute as a cohesive team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We’ve found a way to change that. The integrated team approach - blending designers, developers, and&amp;nbsp;authors together - is no easy task. It requires a mindset shift from thinking about solutions as&amp;nbsp;development-based or content-based to solutions that best serve the user. Only an integrated team can ask&amp;nbsp;the question, “what is best for our users or audience?” and then craft ideas that blend the unique expertise&amp;nbsp;of all of the players involved.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Moving away from a traditional silo’d approach to a more product-based and user-centric one removes&amp;nbsp;barriers between teams. The results they produce are stronger and more strategic because they operate not&amp;nbsp;as competing - or at least isolated - teams to one team working in the best interest of the project.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Building a team like this is the first step and the first thing we’ll cover. We’ll go over what types of&amp;nbsp;individuals and skill-sets are the best and most useful on a team of this type. After that, we’ll discuss&amp;nbsp;ongoing management strategies and tools and tactics that can be used to ensure the ongoing success of&amp;nbsp;the team. Lastly, we’ll also discuss how to leverage analytics to guide ongoing decision making.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
This session will feature a project manager, a strategic communications lead and a technical lead from&amp;nbsp;Adfero who have led an integrated team working on a major Federal website powered by Drupal 7.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;jjones@adfero.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/business-and-strategy&quot;&gt;Business and Strategy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
     <pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2015 16:45:30 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>jjones@adfero.com</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">676 at http://2015.drupalgovcon.org</guid>
  </item>
  <item>
    <title>User Centered Design and Customer Service Oriented Government</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/user-centered-design-and-customer-service-oriented-government</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Federal websites are trending towards more open and user-oriented models thanks to the work of the Federal CIO office and its release of the Digital Services Playbook (&lt;a href=&quot;https://playbook.cio.gov/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;https://playbook.cio.gov/&lt;/a&gt;). It’s an exciting time to working in this space; the government recognizes the need to adopt better practices and more robust solutions for digital work in the name of delivering good citizen services.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Of the many priorities outlined in the playbook, giving users what they need is the most emphasized. This is otherwise known as User-Centered Design or UCD. In the session, we will first discuss how to identify UCD personas and scenarios based on known audience segments and analytics data. Next, we will cover how to apply web-specific UCD tactics to things such as information architecture and functional requirements in a way that complies with federal standards. Lastly, we will cover how to use analytics to constantly drive iterative optimization of a UCD-based project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The session speakers are two federal website architects who’ve recently followed UCD principals to plan and implement Drupal web builds. Bringing experience from the both federal and private website consulting world combined with years of Drupal architecture and development work, they will speak to all aspects of user-centered design from high-level planning down to development best practices.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-slides field--type-file field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Slides:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;file&quot;&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;file-icon&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;application/pdf&quot; src=&quot;/modules/file/icons/application-pdf.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/sites/2015.drupalgovcon.org/files/slides/User%20Centered%20Design%20and%20Customer%20Service%20Oriented%20Government%20JJONES%20CNEIGH.pptx_.pdf&quot; type=&quot;application/pdf; length=803501&quot;&gt;User Centered Design and Customer Service Oriented Government JJONES CNEIGH.pptx_.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;jjones@adfero.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;cneigh@adfero.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-session-timeslot field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Time Slot(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots clearfix&quot; class=&quot;entity entity-field-collection-item field-collection-item-field-event-timeslots&quot;&gt;
