  <item>
    <title>Drupal 7 Taxonomies and the Faceted Search API</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/drupal-7-taxonomies-and-faceted-search-api</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;HealthyPeople.gov allows users to create customizable searches to find data, evidence-based resources and interventions, and community best practices for improving health at the local, state, and national levels. Each of these tools uses Drupal 7 taxonomies and the faceted search API to ensure the consistent usage of terms across the site, as well as to allow content managers to quickly update a term site-wide.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Evidence-Based Resources (EBR) database includes more than 450 EBRs. During the 2014 refresh of the HealthyPeople.gov website in Drupal, a faceted EBR search tool was updated to improve our users’ ability to find relevant resources by various facets, including Healthy People 2020 (HP2020) topic area, strength of evidence, publication date, population characteristics, among other categories. In order to accommodate this search tool, each EBR content type has 12 related taxonomies and links to relevant HP2020 topic area(s) and objective(s). These taxonomies are then fed into the facet API module to allow for faceted search to be displayed on the EBR search page. The combination of these tools allows users to drill down to find resources. During this session, presenters will discuss:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Creating and organizing taxonomies&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Adding taxonomies to content types&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Integrating taxonomies into the Faceted Search API&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Supporting taxonomies in content submission and moderation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Theresa.Devine&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;Matt.Allen&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/site-building&quot;&gt;Site Building&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
     <pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2015 20:05:00 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>Theresa.Devine</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">776 at http://2015.drupalgovcon.org</guid>
  </item>
  <item>
    <title>Case Study: Future-Proofing HHS.gov</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/case-study-future-proofing-hhsgov</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Over the past few years, the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) began its journey to future-proof its content and modernize its website. What began as an effort to create structured content, blossomed into a complete overhaul of HHS.gov to incorporate a mobile-first design and migrate to Drupal in the cloud.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Join us for this panel discussion, where members of the HHS Office of the Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs (ASPA) Digital Communications Division (DCD) and Aquilent teams will discuss the details of the redesign effort, codenamed “Project H.” With its first major release planned for May 2015, learn how the team successfully navigated this multi-phased project and developed the all-new HHS.gov. Topics to be discussed, include:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Content Strategy&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Evaluating CMS Platforms&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Attaining Leadership Buy-In&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mobile-First Approach &amp;amp; Responsive Design&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Content Migration Methodology&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Highly Available &amp;amp; Scalable Infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Beginner&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;ckoroma@hrsa.gov&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;sally.dadjou@hhs.gov&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;arash.farazdaghi@aquilent.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;Samuel.Bronson@hhs.gov&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;natalya.minkovsky@aquilent.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/business-and-strategy&quot;&gt;Business and Strategy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
     <pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2015 20:29:15 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>ckoroma@hrsa.gov</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">791 at http://2015.drupalgovcon.org</guid>
