  <item>
    <title>How Drupal is Transforming Government</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/how-drupal-transforming-government</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Drupal is quickly becoming the de facto standard platform for governments websites, from small towns to the White House.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this session we’ll explore how government agencies are using Drupal to connect citizens, streamline internal operations, increase communication, release open data, lower costs, improve security, and further their missions. Additionally, we’ll dive into the unique challenges and opportunities that exist in working with government agencies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By looking at demos of existing sites we’ll learn how public agencies of all sizes are using Drupal to make a digital platforms of the people, by the people, and for the people, in the 21st century.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Beginner&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;AaronPava&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/business-and-strategy&quot;&gt;Business and Strategy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
     <pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2015 00:27:30 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>AaronPava</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">876 at http://2015.drupalgovcon.org</guid>
  </item>
  <item>
    <title>No One Cares About You </title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/no-one-cares-about-you</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well, that&#039;s the harsh way to say it. But the truth is, the user doesn&#039;t care about you. They care about how your product is going to solve their problem or make their life better. This tiny distinction is often hard for a client to comprehend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&#039;s understandable that after years of hard work, clients want the world to know how wonderful&amp;nbsp;their products / people / process / etc. are. But sometimes this leads to a&amp;nbsp;disconnect between what a client wants to say about themselves and what a user is actually looking for. Performing target market analysis to create&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persona_(user_experience)&quot;&gt;user personas&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;helps bridge this gap and lead to a more user-centered website.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this session we&#039;ll look at the psychology behind this process including :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychographic&quot;&gt;Psychographics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_behaviour&quot;&gt;Consumer Psychology&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Behavioral_economics&quot;&gt;Behavioral Economics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And how to use this data to convince the client that repeating the product name over and over is *not* an effective SEO strategy without resorting to saying &quot;No one cares about you&quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Beginner&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;prynncamm@gmail.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/business-and-strategy&quot;&gt;Business and Strategy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
     <pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2015 02:49:28 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>prynncamm@gmail.com</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">881 at http://2015.drupalgovcon.org</guid>
  </item>
  <item>
    <title>Views Overview for the Beginner</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/views-overview-beginner</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Views is a popular module that can be confusing for the beginner. This session will review some of the important features of Views in Drupal 7 and highlight some additional modules that extend the power of Views.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Topics include:&lt;br /&gt;
How to filter and sort Views results&lt;br /&gt;
How to rewrite outout and setup no results messages&lt;br /&gt;
How to include a view inside another view&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Venn&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item odd&quot;&gt;mdandelion&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/site-building&quot;&gt;Site Building&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
