  <item>
    <title>Aegir: A Drupal-As-A-Service Secret Weapon</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/aegir-drupal-service-secret-weapon</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;iframe frameborder=&quot;0&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/vsAOjP5iIhQ&quot; width=&quot;420&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;When it comes to site migrations, few platforms rival the ease and efficiency of Drupal. But what if you could make a Drupal&amp;nbsp;migration&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;even easier?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;In this session, Mobomo will discuss wielding Aegir to create a secure, scalable architecture to manage multiple Drupal sites through one, single interface. Participants will learn:&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;how to execute quick, seamless site deployments;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;how to automate implementations maximizing Amazon Cloud&amp;nbsp;capabilities; and&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;how to&amp;nbsp;design and build award-winning, massive migrations—all while leveraging Aegir.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
