  <item>
    <title>How To Prepare for Drupal 8</title>
    <link>http://2015.drupalgovcon.org/drupal-govcon-2015/sessions/how-prepare-drupal-8</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;One question that everybody in Drupal community has on their minds is how do we prepare for Drupal 8. This is a question that is common with both&amp;nbsp;client managers and&amp;nbsp;development&amp;nbsp;shops. We will discuss few learnings we have had over the last 8 months building with D8; and the challenges that the team had to overcome. Also, we will explain our rationale of choosing to build with D8 for client project.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This session will be useful to a variety of audience, and some sample points that will talk about during the session.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developers :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Accept the fact that developing in Drupal 8 is going to be like learning a new platform altogether.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Get comfortable with Object Oriented Programming.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Get to know about scaffolding. Believe us you are gonna use it time and again in Drupal 8.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Site Admins :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;You can still go ahead and use Drupal 7 if you feel that you do not have enough support in Drupal 8 for modules that you frequently use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Teams&amp;nbsp;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Consider when would be a right time to upgrade to Drupal 8.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ask your dev team to slowly replace the existing modules with modules which have a proper upgrade path to Drupal and have similar interfaces as that of Drupal 8. This makes sure that when your sites are migrated to Drupal 8, there is not much change in user-experience.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Allocate a decent budget for the migration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;May you have greater adventures with Drupal 8 ;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-experience field--type-list-text field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;Intermediate&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-field-speakers field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Speaker(s):&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;mohan@azrisolutions.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field--name-og-vocabulary field--type-entityreference field--label-above&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__label&quot;&gt;Session Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field__item even&quot;&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Session Tracks (Drupal GovCon 2015)&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/session-tracks-drupal-govcon-2015/business-and-strategy&quot;&gt;Business and Strategy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
     <pubDate>Sat, 18 Apr 2015 03:02:41 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator>mohan@azrisolutions.com</dc:creator>
 <guid isPermaLink="false">1146 at http://2015.drupalgovcon.org</guid>
